- "blossomed into high-quality productions" refers to videos with an average MOS greater than 3.5;
- MOS, PSNR, and SSIM are metrics used to evaluate video quality, with higher values generally indicating better quality;
- The average MOS is calculated by averaging the MOS values of all representations of a video.

- 'High' quality videos have both top 3 bitrate and rebuffering duration rankings;
- 'Medium' quality videos have both top 6 bitrate and rebuffering duration rankings;
- 'Low' quality videos have either bitrate or rebuffering duration rankings outside the top 6.

- "Active" status indicates that the video is currently in use or available;
- "Framerate" refers to the number of frames per second in a video;
- "Video bitrate" is the amount of data used per second of video, typically measured in bits per second.

- 'Popular videos' refers to videos with a high average bitrate;
- 'High average bitrate' is defined as greater than 500;
- 'Viewed' is determined by the number of access logs.

- Engagement is the sum of views and downloads;
- Mean Opinion Score (MOS) is a measure of video quality on a scale from 1 to 5;
- Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio (PSNR) is a measure of the quality of reconstruction of a signal, with higher values indicating better quality;
- Structural Similarity Index (SSIM) is a measure of the structural similarity between two images, with 1 being a perfect match;
- The average report value is a metric from user feedback reports, with higher values indicating better user satisfaction.

- The `video_bitrate` is a measure of the amount of data used to encode a video, typically measured in bits per second;
- The `report_type` can be daily, weekly, or monthly, reflecting the frequency with which the reports are generated;
- The overall average `metric_value` of `video_bitrate` is calculated across all reports, regardless of their type.

- Rebuffering issues refer to pauses or interruptions in video playback, often due to network issues or server delays;
- Daily reports are generated to provide a daily summary of video quality metrics;
- User access type 'view' indicates that a user has viewed the report or the data within it.

sql:
SELECT report_date, report_type
FROM video_quality_reports
WHERE report_type = 'weekly' AND status = 'published';

SELECT AVG(qm.vmaf) AS overall_avg_vmaf
FROM quality_metrics qm
JOIN representations r ON qm.representation_id = r.representation_id;

SELECT SUM(qm.psnr) AS total_psnr
FROM quality_metrics qm
JOIN representations r ON qm.representation_id = r.representation_id;

SELECT metric_value
FROM report_metrics
WHERE metric_name = 'rebuffering_duration';
